32:19.638 --> 32:21.439 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Lisa and Dan.

32:21.473 --> 32:26.678 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Lisa, thanks for joining us.

32:26.711 --> 32:30.849 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: My pleasure.

32:30.882 --> 32:38.723 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: The tourist season
in Europe is
winding down, and at least one
nation hopes

32:38.757 --> 32:40.792 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it will stay that way.

32:40.826 --> 32:45.664 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Iceland was one of this year's
it destinations
for vacationers, but people
there are learning

32:45.697 --> 32:47.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the downside of that boom.

32:47.866 --> 32:51.536 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
More tourist money can also mean
more problems.

32:51.570 --> 32:56.541 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Special correspondent Malcolm
Brabant has
our story.

32:56.575 --> 33:10.021 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: With its
volcanic underbelly
and unspoiled prehistoric
landscape, Iceland

33:10.055 --> 33:12.958 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has suddenly become one of the
hottest destinations.

33:12.991 --> 33:16.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
OLOF YRR ATLADOTTIR, Director
General, Icelandic
Tourist Board: My name is Olof
Yrr Atladottir.

33:16.928 --> 33:19.698 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I'm the director general of
the Icelandic
Tourist Board.

33:19.731 --> 33:27.672 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
For me, Iceland is the
possibility of enjoying
solitude in spectacular
wide-open spaces.

33:27.706 --> 33:30.442 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Iceland is
certainly spectacular.

33:30.475 --> 33:36.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Gullfoss Waterfall, part of
the so-called
Golden Circle of attractions not
far from

33:36.047 --> 33:40.185 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the capital, is said by some to
rival Niagara
Falls.

33:40.218 --> 33:42.921 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And it's not surrounded by
high-rise hotels.

33:42.954 --> 33:45.657 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But can you get solitude?

33:45.690 --> 33:46.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's debatable.

33:46.791 --> 33:48.860 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Iceland is a location for "Game
of Thrones."

33:48.894 --> 33:55.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And fans of the hit series are
partly responsible
for the island's new popularity,
so much so,

33:55.200 --> 34:00.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that it's difficult to grab a
shot of pure
nature without getting
photo-bombed by people

34:00.872 --> 34:02.073 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
taking selfies.

34:02.107 --> 34:03.375 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK HEASMAN, Charity Director:
My name is
Mark Heasman.

34:03.408 --> 34:05.243 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I run a children's charity in
London.

34:05.277 --> 34:06.645 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's a delightful country.

34:06.678 --> 34:08.580 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So far, we have been in
Reykjavik.

34:08.613 --> 34:12.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we're now just about to go
out on a three-week
expedition around the interior,
so we can't

34:12.417 --> 34:14.252 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
wait to get away from the
people.

34:14.286 --> 34:18.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: We met Heasman
in the Thingvellir
National Park, another
destination on the

34:19.024 --> 34:21.192 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Golden Circle route.

34:21.226 --> 34:26.898 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a World Heritage Site and
place of great
national importance to
Icelanders as a legendary

34:26.932 --> 34:28.934 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
meeting point throughout the
centuries.

34:28.967 --> 34:32.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARK HEASMAN: This particular
point seems
really crowded, actually, for
somewhere that's

34:33.004 --> 34:35.707 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
so special and so unique.

34:35.740 --> 34:38.610 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's actually a bit
disappointing to see it
full of tourists.

34:38.643 --> 34:40.612 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But then people need to see it,
I guess.

34:40.645 --> 34:43.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Fishing used to
be Iceland's
most important industry.

34:43.615 --> 34:49.654 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's now been overtaken by
tourism, which
accounts for a third of all of
the country's

34:49.688 --> 34:51.556 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
foreign currency earnings.

34:51.589 --> 34:57.195 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Since 2010, there's been between
a 25 percent
to 30 percent increase in the
number of visitors

34:57.228 --> 34:58.863 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
each year.

34:58.897 --> 35:04.135 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so, this year, 2016, looks
like being
a record season, with government
agencies

35:04.169 --> 35:05.737 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
predicting 1.8 million arrivals.

35:05.770 --> 35:09.975 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IAN SYKES, Resident of Iceland:
My name is
Ian Sykes.

35:10.008 --> 35:14.145 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm a retired lecturer in
hospitality and
tourism from Scotland.

35:14.179 --> 35:18.650 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I now live in Iceland just
outside Reykjavik
with my wife.

35:18.683 --> 35:20.719 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And I run a guest house here.

35:20.752 --> 35:24.756 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I believe Iceland really needs
to get a grip
of tourism.

35:24.789 --> 35:26.391 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Get a hold of it.

35:26.424 --> 35:29.394 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And if it really hurts,
actually, it might
hurt.

35:29.427 --> 35:32.230 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just control the numbers and get
everything
sorted.

35:32.263 --> 35:38.503 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At the moment, it's just more
and more tourists
and money in the till, without a
real thought

35:38.536 --> 35:39.871 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to the future.

35:39.904 --> 35:41.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
OLOF YRR ATLADOTTIR: I think
that the growth
has been very rapid.

35:41.406 --> 35:43.908 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it is very challenging to
meet such a
rapid growth.

35:43.942 --> 35:47.145 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And, yes, we have had growing
pains, yes.

35:47.178 --> 35:53.351 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
However, Iceland is still full
of spots where
you can still enjoy the
solitude.

35:53.385 --> 35:58.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are a few places that
become like other
most popular tourism
destinations, like the

35:59.024 --> 36:02.160 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Eiffel Tower in Paris or these
hot spots.

36:02.193 --> 36:06.031 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They tend to become crowded in
Iceland, as
in other places.

36:06.064 --> 36:10.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Iceland still provides the
possibility
for a very singular experience.

36:10.068 --> 36:14.773 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GUNNAR THOR JOHANNESSON,
University of Iceland:
My name is Gunnar Thor
Johannesson.

36:14.806 --> 36:20.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I'm a professor in geography and
tourism at
the University of Iceland,
Reykjavik.

36:20.345 --> 36:26.217 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
My specialty is tourism
development, tourism
policy and planning, and
destination development.

36:26.251 --> 36:30.755 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need to invest, like, in soft
things like
knowledge.

36:30.789 --> 36:32.924 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We need to invest in education
and training.

36:32.957 --> 36:36.394 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need to invest in -- also in
concrete and
steel.

36:36.428 --> 36:39.564 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We need to invest -- like, in
the road system.

36:39.597 --> 36:44.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We know that some of the more
serious challenges
that tourism is facing is that
simply that

36:44.469 --> 36:49.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
some of the infrastructure in
some of the
hot spots of tourism is not
strong enough.

36:49.707 --> 36:54.446 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
IAN SYKES: The radical kind of
answer would
be to put a ceiling on the
number of people

36:54.479 --> 37:00.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that come, until we're really
quite happy
that we have the infrastructure
to cope, because,

37:00.652 --> 37:05.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at the moment, people are coming
on short
three-day holidays, enjoy
Iceland, but are

37:05.590 --> 37:11.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
going away saying fantastic
country, but it's
expensive, and there are no
toilets, and it's

37:11.496 --> 37:13.298 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
all crowded.

37:13.331 --> 37:17.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
OLOF YRR ATLADOTTIR: I actually
don't think
that's very possible, because
that it would

37:17.068 --> 37:23.708 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
mean putting a cap on private
enterprise in
a way, in a very strange sort of
way.

37:23.741 --> 37:25.944 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I don't think that I would
believe in
that.

37:25.977 --> 37:32.217 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I do think that we can both
organize and
plan certain destinations within
Iceland.

37:32.250 --> 37:38.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, of course, if we look
towards the industry,
which is a very wide industry,
has very, very

37:38.590 --> 37:45.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
many aspects, and I think that
in a way we
can maybe organize the tourism
so it grows,

37:45.497 --> 37:47.632 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
as I say, more harmoniously.

37:47.665 --> 37:53.071 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
HALLDOR MAR, Resident of
Iceland: My name
is Halldor Mar.

37:53.104 --> 37:55.507 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'm a graphic design student.

37:55.540 --> 37:59.210 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I'm about to get booted out
of my home
because of Airbnb.

37:59.244 --> 38:04.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The shortage of
hotels and
guest houses in Iceland has led
to an explosion

38:04.883 --> 38:10.755 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of residents renting out their
homes to tourists
using the Airbnb Web site.

38:10.788 --> 38:16.327 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Halldor Mar doesn't believe that
new legislation
tightening the rules on Airbnb
rentals will

38:16.361 --> 38:18.329 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
help potential tenants.

38:18.363 --> 38:23.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
