account for
70 percent of his earnings,
which tempers

38:23.268 --> 38:25.537 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
his enthusiasm for the tourist
influx.

38:25.570 --> 38:30.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HALLDOR MAR: They're taking away
our homes,
you know?

38:30.275 --> 38:31.643 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's good that they're coming.

38:31.676 --> 38:33.645 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But it's not really their fault.

38:33.678 --> 38:38.650 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't think they're aware of
the problem.

38:38.683 --> 38:45.823 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But the landlords, just
everybody here wants
to make money and get into the
market, tourism

38:45.857 --> 38:46.824 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
market.

38:46.858 --> 38:47.892 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And that's the problem.

38:47.926 --> 38:48.826 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ASHILDUR BRAGADOTTI, Director,
Reykjavik:
Hi.

38:48.860 --> 38:49.827 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
My name is Ashildur Bragadotti.

38:49.861 --> 38:51.362 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I'm the director of Visit
Reykjavik.

38:51.396 --> 38:55.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We are not facing any problems,
in my opinion.

38:55.567 --> 39:01.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, of course, we have to be
concerned because
the growth has been so much,
more than anyone

39:01.139 --> 39:03.541 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
could have expected.

39:03.575 --> 39:07.979 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there are some challenges
that we're facing
because of that.

39:08.012 --> 39:12.984 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It takes, like, two to three
years to build
a hotel.

39:13.017 --> 39:19.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Therefore, Airbnb has become
more common in
Reykjavik, and that's something
that -- a

39:19.624 --> 39:21.492 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
question that we're facing now.

39:21.526 --> 39:27.198 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Are there too many citizens
lending out their
houses?

39:27.232 --> 39:33.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GUNNAR THOR JOHANNESSON: I think
it's also
positive not to ban Airbnb
altogether.

39:33.271 --> 39:35.006 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
